race.comment: The Trinder yard has strong representation. ROUNDLE PARK (5) held on well beaten half a length fresh from a spell over 1200m at Launceston as favourite. He'd come off a big Maiden win at this track and is back in grade with a handy 3kg claim. Flies here and can go one better. PRINCE OF KHATUN (4) brings a string of narrow defeats from the turf and won his only start this course/trip. His numbers stack right up, and he has an inside barrier and a handy 3kg claim. MISS LYRA (7) resumes with Byrne Burke engaged. She just missed in a Hobart Open 2 when last seen and has trialled well for her return. Has an awkward gate but should be running into it. STAR FORTIAN (11) peaks and led and comfortably won her Maiden here fresh three back. Has been given a freshen and has the blinkers on for the first time. Newitt rides and will use the inside barrier. Keep onside.
